&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales and Account Managers to prioritize technical service needs, supporting both account retention and new business development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide hands-on technical expertise, including plant evaluations, jar testing, and trial support, to optimize customer solutions and drive growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the strategy, development, and performance of wastewater product lines to meet evolving application needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage product lifecycle and profitability, including formulations, pricing, margin optimization, and new product development (Optiva projects).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and continuously improve the Water Treatment Product Resource Master to ensure accuracy and accessibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Purchasing to optimize inventory levels, reduce costs, and enhance product performance, including identifying alternative suppliers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with chemical suppliers to source innovative, cost-effective solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a key liaison across internal teams (Technical Center, Equipment Group, Purchasing, Product Information) to align resources and deliver seamless support.&lt;/li&gt
